title: Episode dated 7 February 1996
description: California has allowed carrying of concealed weapons. A sane decision that aids public safety or a sure path to more shootings and even more insecurity? Also, the latest fad in America is hiring a personal life coach. Baby boomers' fault?

title: Episode dated 2 May 1997
description: Topic: Supreme Court upheld a ban on billboards promoting cigarettes and alcohol in Baltimore. Is protecting the kids from vices in this way effective or is it not only counterproductive but an attack on freedom of speech?
